OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FThe Welsh Rugby Union is fighting
OL,8,Fmultiple legal battles, its Chair is
OL,9,Ffacing a vote of no confidence.
OL,11,FOne of Welsh rugby's four regions -
OL,12,Fthe Ospreys - is on the brink of
OL,13,Fextinction. The senior men's national
OL,14,Fside had lost 26 of its last 28
OL,15,Fmatches.
OL,17,FThis was the backdrop to Italy's visit
OL,18,Fto the Principality Stadium.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FBut despite the maelstrom of turmoil
OL,8,Fand toxicity that swirled above the
OL,9,Froof of this great stadium, Steve
OL,10,FTandy's side summoned a performance
OL,11,Fthat could prove to be a defining
OL,12,Fmoment.
OL,14,FThey roared to their first Six Nations
OL,15,Fvictory since March 2023, thumping
OL,16,FItaly 31-17.
OL,18,FThe opening exchanges were tense. Both
OL,19,Fsides knew that conceding the
OL,20,Fascendancy early could prove
OL,21,Fparticularly damaging.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FWales had more of the early possession
OL,8,Fbut never really looked like doing
OL,9,Fanything with it. The style of play
OL,10,Fwas risk-averse, and defences were on
OL,11,Ftop.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FThe game sparked into life around the
OL,8,F10-minute mark. Italy turned the ball
OL,9,Fover on their own 10-metre line and
OL,10,FTommaso Menoncello stormed up field.
OL,11,FThe move ended with a crucial Joe
OL,12,FHawkins turnover deep inside his own
OL,13,F22.Paolo Garbisi then missed what
OL,14,Fwould be deemed a relative sitter at
OL,15,Fthis level and then the crowd had
OL,16,Fsomething to shout about.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FEllis Mee did brilliantly to turn and
OL,8,Fgather a loose ball close to his line
OL,9,Funder heavy pressure from Monty Ioane.
OL,10,FHe fed Louis Rees-Zammit, who launched
OL,11,Fa booming clearance deep into Italy's
OL,12,Fhalf. The chase was hard and Mee was
OL,13,Fthe one who got in over the ball to
OL,14,Fwin a penalty.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FFrom there Wales kicked to the corner
OL,8,Fand sent Eddie James charging into the
OL,9,FItalian line. The ball was quick and
OL,10,FAaron Wainwright was next to throw his
OL,11,Fsignificant bulk at the visitors. The
OL,12,Fline broke and the Wales No.8 dived
OL,13,Fover for the opening score.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FItaly soon worked another dangerous
OL,8,Fposition, instigated by some shrewd
OL,9,Fdefensive work from Juan Ignacio Brex.
OL,10,FBut Garbisi's offload went to the deck
OL,11,Fand Wales survived another onslaught.A
OL,12,Fscrum penalty compounded by another at
OL,13,Fa breakdown gave Dan Edwards the
OL,14,Fopportunity to put Wales five metres
OL,15,Fout. He duly obliged.
OL,17,FWales brought down the initial shunt
OL,18,Fthemselves but Wainwright was on hand
OL,19,Fto burrow his way over from close
OL,20,Frange. Edwards' conversion doubled his
OL,21,Fside's tally.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FAs the game approached the half hour
OL,8,Fmark, Wales were dictating. The
OL,9,Fvisitors overthrew a lineout, Wales
OL,10,Fgrubbered through. Rees-Zammit sped
OL,11,Fafter Ioane and a wave of red bodies
OL,12,Fpiled into the ruck, leading to an
OL,13,Finevitable penalty deep in the Italian
OL,14,F22.
OL,16,FThe driving maul carried skipper Dewi
OL,17,FLake over the line for Wales' third
OL,18,Ftry. It was a score that put Wales in
OL,19,Fcomplete control, a position they had
OL,20,Flittle experience of but seemed to be
OL,21,Frelishing.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FWhen Rhys Carre snaffled a counter-
OL,8,Fattacking Lorenzo Pani and won a
OL,9,Fturnover penalty, the Principality
OL,10,FStadium erupted as if a try had been
OL,11,Fscored. But this time Italy withstood
OL,12,Fthe Wales offensive deep in the
OL,13,Fvisiting 22.
OL,15,FSteve Tandy's side didn't add to their
OL,16,Ftally before the break but they were
OL,17,Fcruising when Christophe Ridley
OL,18,Fbrought the first half to a close.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FItaly, for all their exploits earlier
OL,8,Fin this tournament, offered very
OL,9,Flittle and would have to do some soul-
OL,10,Fsearching at half time.
OL,12,FWhen you've lost 26 out of your last
OL,13,F28 matches, no lead feels safe. But
OL,14,FWales could not have dreamt of putting
OL,15,Fthemselves in a better position after
OL,16,F40 minutes, leading 21-0.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FWainwright and Lake, Wales' standout
OL,8,Fperformers in this Championship, led
OL,9,Fthe charge early in the second half.
OL,10,FThey carried numerous times, making
OL,11,Fdent after dent, in a flowing move
OL,12,Fthat ended with fly-half Edwards
OL,13,Farcing his way to the line for a bonus-
OL,14,Fpoint try.
OL,16,FMoments later he clipped over a drop
OL,17,Fgoal from 45 metres, stretching Wales'
OL,18,Flead out to 31 points. It was turning
OL,19,Finto a significant afternoon in his
OL,20,FTest career after a challenging period
OL,21,Fin the No.10 jersey.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FBut it wasn't all plain sailing.
OL,8,FThings would soon get complicated. A
OL,9,Fscrum penalty put Italy in a dangerous
OL,10,Fposition and their driving maul
OL,11,Frumbled towards the line. Over it went
OL,12,Fwith Tommaso Di Bartolomeo touching
OL,13,Fdown. But despite the try, replacement
OL,14,Fprop Archie Griffin was sent to the
OL,15,Fsin bin for cynically collapsing the
OL,16,Fmaul.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FWales weathered the storm. Italy did
OL,8,Fget over the line but were held up
OL,9,Fjust as Griffin was preparing to come
OL,10,Fonto the field. They won another
OL,11,Fpenalty on their own 10 metre line and
OL,12,Fas the tight-head returned to the
OL,13,Ffield, he was coming on to an
OL,14,Fattacking lineout in the 22.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FBut it was Italy who would score next.
OL,8,FMenoncello, who had been
OL,9,Funcharacteristically quiet, was the
OL,10,Fcatalyst and made the initial break.
OL,11,FItaly streamed through and, despite
OL,12,Fsome stubborn tackling, Tommaso Allan
OL,13,Fwrestled his way over for his side's
OL,14,Fsecond score.
OL,16,FThe hosts were clearly feeling the
OL,17,Feffects of their efforts earlier in
OL,18,Fthe match and a long tournament looked
OL,19,Fto be catching up to them, with
OL,20,Fplayers receiving treatment for aching
OL,21,Flimbs at each break in play.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G14/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FItaly were finishing stronger and were
OL,8,Fdenied a third when Mee just about
OL,9,Fmanaged to get Ioane into touch before
OL,10,Fthe latter grounded the ball. With
OL,11,Fless than 10 minutes on the clock and
OL,12,FWales three scores ahead, even with
OL,13,Fall that had come before, surely the
OL,14,Fresult was beyond doubt.
OL,16,FDespite the inevitability surrounding
OL,17,Fthe result, Italy kept coming.
OL,18,FLeonardo Marin thought he'd crossed
OL,19,Fbut he too was denied after TMO Mike
OL,20,FAdamson adjudged his grounding of the
OL,21,Fball to be short of the line.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G15/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FEventually the third Italian try did
OL,8,Fcome through Garbisi but it mattered
OL,9,Fnot.
OL,11,FThe result might not lift Wales off
OL,12,Fthe bottom of the Six Nations table,
OL,13,Fbut it is a win that may carry
OL,14,Fsignificance in other ways and that
OL,15,Fwas evident in the celebrations of
OL,16,Fplayers who have almost no experience
OL,17,Fof what it's like to win at this level.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G16/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1773760267
OL,3,CWales roar to first Six Nations win in
OL,4,Cthree years after 31-17 thumping of
OL,5,CItaly
OL,7,FWhat happens next will determine just
OL,8,Fhow significant this is but as players
OL,9,Fleft the field, they did so with
OL,10,Fflickers of confidence in their own
OL,11,Fability to compete at this level and a
OL,12,Fsense that this could be the turning
OL,13,Fpoint for a young group finding their
OL,14,Fway.
OL,16,FWales: Louis Rees-Zammit; Ellis Mee,
OL,17,FEddie James, Joe Hawkins, Josh Adams;
OL,18,FDan Edwards, Tomos Williams; Rhys
OL,19,FCarre, Dewi Lake (C), Tomas Francis;
OL,20,FDafydd Jenkins, Ben Carter; Alex Mann,
OL,21,FJames Botham, Aaron Wainwright.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G17/19
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
